ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: It was interesting but covered a broad range of topics in little detail.
It teaches all aspects of biochem and biophy, and is quite interesting.
You learn about of a lot of biophysics and biochemistry experiment and at the end you design an experiment using those techniques.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: The course excels in exposing students to new technologies and methods.
It shows me many different aspects of conducting biological research and broadens my horizons.
I plan to use a lot of the experiments that I proposed in my final paper.
Covers a multitude of widely used techniques that most of us will not be exposed to during our lab work. This course at least makes us aware of the existence of said techniques
